    <p class="section-number">09 · Frequently Asked Questions</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Commercial repair, what operators ask us</h2>

    <div class="faq-list">
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>What commercial appliances do you repair in Los Angeles?</h3>
        <p>Commercial reach-in and walk-in refrigerators and freezers, commercial ice machines, commercial convection ovens and ranges, commercial dishwashers, and commercial washers and dryers. Brands include True, Turbo Air, Beverage-Air, Vulcan, Garland, Manitowoc, Hoshizaki, Hobart, and Speed Queen.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>How quickly can you respond to a commercial emergency?</h3>
        <p>Same day for most calls before noon, next morning for afternoon calls. Refrigeration failures are our highest-priority commercial call, we understand a cooler above 41°F has a countdown on it. Call (323) 870-4790 and describe the equipment and urgency.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>Do you service True, Turbo Air, and Beverage-Air commercial refrigerators?</h3>
        <p>Yes. These are the three commercial refrigeration brands we see most often in LA restaurants and food businesses. We carry OEM True parts on the van and source parts for the others through commercial distributors. We're EPA 608 certified for refrigerant work.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>My commercial refrigerator is not holding temperature, is my food at risk?</h3>
        <p>If it's above 41°F, move temperature-sensitive inventory immediately. Document the temperature and time. Call us, refrigeration failures are our highest-priority commercial call. We carry parts for True, Turbo Air, and Beverage-Air on the van.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>Do you offer preventive maintenance contracts?</h3>
        <p>Yes. For restaurants, ghost kitchens, hotels, and multi-unit operators, we offer scheduled maintenance visits, condenser coil cleaning, refrigerant checks, door gasket inspection, ice machine descaling. Regular maintenance prevents the failures that shut you down on a Saturday night.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>What commercial appliances are outside your scope?</h3>
        <p>Rational and Alto-Shaam combi ovens (require factory authorization), Hobart industrial mixers and slicers, large commercial HVAC. For these, we'll tell you directly and refer you to the right specialist, that's honest service, not a limitation.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

